    <element name="Crafting" type="Class Feature" source="Final Fantasy XIV DND Compendium" id="ID_FFXIV_CLASS_FEATURE_NOVICECRAFTING">
        <description>
            <p>You gain access to a Crafting Profession. You can only select one Crafting Profession and will advance them at higher levels. You will be able to craft items from your Crafting Profession from the Novice Crafting List. Visit the respective profession guild and aquire your tools.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">Alchemist</h5>
            <p>Alchemists are masters of powders and potions – grinding and blending materials to produce useful consumables, elixirs, inks, wands, and grimoires.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">Armorer</h5>
            <p>Armorers excel at shaping metals and ores into equipable heavy armor - such as chainmail, ring mail, scale mail and plate body armor.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">Blacksmith</h5>
            <p>Blacksmiths specialize in the refining of metals and the production of main-hand and off-hand equipment, such as swords, axes, scythes, guns, and more.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">Carpenter</h5>
            <p>Carpenters excel at the production of wooden materials, furniture and equipment used by many classes in the game, such as clogs, bows, staves and polearms.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">Culinarian</h5>
            <p>Culinarians utilize various ingredients to create hearty and emboldening meals. Characters can consume food to receive temporary buffs to a variety of attributes.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">Goldsmith</h5>
            <p>Goldsmiths bend metals and gems into fashionable accessories and bejewelled weaponry. Many classes desire their fineries, such as rings, bracelets, necklaces, chakrams(dancer), nouliths(sage) and crystal mediums(red mage).</p>
            <h5 class="caption">Leatherworker</h5>
            <p>Leatherworkers prepare hides, pelts and furs from Eorzea's most notorious monsters into leather-based medium armor and accessories.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">Weaver</h5>
            <p>Weavers convert fabrics and fibres into comfortably light armor and accessories, such as robes, ribbons, shirts and pantaloons.</p>
        </description>
        <rules>
            <select type="Class Feature" name="Crafting Profession" supports="Gunbreaker" level="1"/>
        </rules>
    </element>
